.TH createRuler  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBcreateRuler\fR \-  Adds a ruler
.SH Syntax \fBcreateRuler\fR  [-help]   {{-center {<x y>} -radius <value>} | -coordinates {<x1 y1 x2 y2>
...}}
.P Adds a ruler. For an orthogonal ruler, use -coordinates to specify ruler segments. For a circular ruler, use -center and -radius. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each createRuler parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:   man createRuler  "\fB-center {<x y>}\fR" Specifies the coordinates for the center of a circular ruler.    "\fB-coordinates {<x1 y1 x2 y2
...>}\fR" Specifies the beginning and ending coordinates for the ruler line segments. The values are in microns.  "\fB-radius <value>\fR" Specifies the radius of a circular ruler. The value is of type float. 
.SH Example
.RS  "*" 2 The following command creates a circular ruler of radius 500 with the center at {0 0}:  createRuler -center {0 0} -radius 500
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 clearAllRulers
.RE
.RS  "*" 2 The Main Window chapter of Menu Reference
.RS  "*" 2 Toolbar Widgets
.RE  "*" 2 Tools Menu chapter of Menu Reference
.RS  "*" 2 Create Ruler  "*" 2 Clear All Rulers
.RE 
.RE
.P
